							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/george-makari/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/gm_crop-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="George Makari" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/george-makari/">George Makari</a></h6>
										George Makari is the author of three books, including <em>Soul Machine: The Invention of the Modern Mind</em> and <em>Of Fear and Strangers: A History of Xenophobia</em>. His articles have appeared in <em>The New Yorker</em>, <em>The Atlantic</em>, and <em>The New York Times</em>.																			</div>
